    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes a technique for creating the illusion of continuous tones or color depth by mixing dots of color from a limited palette. The term is generally used in the context of digital imaging or computer graphics, and can be applied to color or black and white images.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000009221/Cotton and Oliver, Cyberspace Lexicon (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047566/Newton's Telecom Dictionary (2000)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>形容一種從色彩有限之調色板裡混合色點以創造連續色調或色深幻覺的技巧。此術語通常用於數位成像或電腦繪圖，也可應用於彩色或黑白影像。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beschrijft een techniek die de illusie van continue tonen of kleurdiepte creëert door het mengen van gekleurde stippen van een beperkt kleurenpalet. De term wordt meestal gebruikt in de context van digitale beeldbewerking of computergraphics en kan worden toegepast op kleur- of zwart-witafbeeldingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Descreve uma técnica para criar a ilusão de tons contínuos ou profundidade de cor misturando pontos de cor de uma paleta limitada. O termo é geralmente usado no contexto de imagens digitais ou computação gráfica, e pode ser aplicado a imagens coloridas ou em preto e branco.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
